Shareable: A nonprofit media outlet and action network promoting sharing-based solutions for a more resilient and equitable world.  
P2P Foundation: Researches, documents, and promotes peer-to-peer practices in a variety of fields.  
Commons Network: Think tank promoting access to knowledge and other social and ecological causes from a commons perspective.  
Regeneration International: Promotes food, farming and land use systems that regenerate and stabilize climate systems, the health of the planet and people.  
The Biomimicry Institute: Empowers people to create nature-inspired solutions for a healthy planet.  
Ellen MacArthur Foundation: Promotes the transition to a circular economy, where waste and pollution are designed out.  
Post-Growth Institute: An international group exploring and inspiring paths to global prosperity that don't rely on economic growth.  
The Natural Step: Helps organizations and individuals understand and move towards sustainability.  
Presencing Institute: Develops awareness-based methodologies for leadership and change.  
Regenesis Group: Provides regenerative development services to create vitality in human and natural systems.  
Capital Institute: Explores and promotes economic transition strategies aligned with living systems principles.  
Commonspoly: A board game teaching principles of commoning and cooperation, in contrast to monopolistic practices.  
Dark Matter Labs: Designs institutional infrastructure for a distributed, democratic and sustainable next economy.  
The Next System Project: Promotes visions, models and pathways that point to a "next system" radically different from today's failed systems.  
Platform Cooperativism Consortium: Supports the development of a more democratic digital economy.  
Participatory City Foundation: Works on large-scale practical participatory ecosystem approaches to city transformation.